content.body:
### Shop 185/65R14 Tire Size
185/65R14 tires can be found on coupes and sedans from the late 90s to mid-2000s. If you drive a Chevrolet Prizm, Dodge Neon, Ford Focus, Honda Civic, Hyundai Accent, Kia Rio, Mitsubishi Lancer, Nissan Versa, Suzuki Aerio, or Toyota Corolla from that timeframe then there’s a chance you ride had 185/65R14 tires, and a new version of any of these vehicles might’ve rolled out of the factory with a set of Goodyear Integrity, [Kumho Solus KH16](https://simpletire.com/brands/kumho-tires/solus-kh16), Yokohama Y376R, Bridgestone B381, Bridgestone Potenza RE92 tires attached.

Popular vehicles include:
1998-2002 Chevrolet Prizm
1995-2002 Dodge Neon
2000-2004 Ford Focus
1996-2000 Honda Civic
2006-2011 Hyundai Accent
2006-2011 Kia Rio
2002-2005 Mitsubishi Lancer
2009-2011 Nissan Versa
2002-2007 Suzuki Aerio
1993-2002 Toyota Corolla

Most drivers only use one set of tires, making all-season tires a common choice thanks to their ability to perform in dry, wet, and light winter weather conditions. Check out the Falken Sincera SN250 A/S, Toyo Extensa A/S II, and [Nexen N’Priz AH8](https://simpletire.com/brands/nexen-tires/n-priz-ah8) if you need a set of 185/65R14 tires that can be used year-round.

While all-season tires can be used year-round, they might struggle in heavy ice, slush, and snow. Fortunately, winter tires are engineered to perform in these conditions, and tires like the Hankook Winter i cept iZ2 (W616) and [GT Radial IcePro 3](https://simpletire.com/brands/gt-radial-tires/icepro-3) are more than capable of getting through tough winter weather.

Whether you drive a Honda Civic, Hyundai Accent, Nissan Versa, or something else, SimpleTire has a set of 185/65R14 tires that meets your needs at a great price!
